         Okay, given that it's not a fake..</P><P>Back when they removed the original hell levels, I bashed folks who complained about it.  It was a matter of serious burn out, personally.</P><P>/shrug</P><P>Experience teaching otherwise, I don't know if I like the idea of the other hell levels being removed. Don't get me wrong, 59 going the way of the DoDo would be great for me, but I have ran into <i>so many</i> newbs now post 50...</P><P>Sigh, I have become <b>so</b> jaded.</P><P>As for fighting monsters even or greater and getting better experience for it, why bother? Practically speaking, where are you going to do this the most?  In my opinion, raids.  Who's going to benefit? The KS group.  Day to day gaming I see this as doing squat.</P><P>Flurry, rampage, summoning, uber spells, quad for hundreds, so forth.  Why bother, when you can go through more blue cons for, probably, at least close to equal experience with less deaths and trouble?</P><P>~Mysk</P><P>Baron Mysk<BR><span style="filter:progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Glow(Color=#d45bf9,Strength=7); width: 0px; color: brown">Tunare</span><BR><a href="http://www.myskyra.net" target="_blank">http://www.myskyra.net</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
